TY  - JOUR
AU  - Acharya, Viral V.
AU  - Lambrecht, Bart M.
T1  - A Theory of Income Smoothing When Insiders Know More Than Outsiders
PY  - 2015
Y1  - 2015/09/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhv026
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 28
IS  - 9
SP  - 2534
EP  - 2574
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We develop a theory of income and payout smoothing by firms when insiders know more about income than outside shareholders, but property rights ensure that outsiders can enforce a fair payout. Insiders set payout to meet outsiders' expectations and underproduce to manage future expectations downward. The observed income and payout process are smooth and adjust partially and over time in response to economic shocks. The smaller the inside ownership, the more severe underproduction is, resulting in an “outside equity Laffer curve.”
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhv026
ER  - 



