TY  - JOUR
AU  - Gale, Douglas
AU  - Gottardi, Piero
T1  - Capital Structure, Investment, and Fire Sales
PY  - 2015
Y1  - 2015/09/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhv016
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 28
IS  - 9
SP  - 2502
EP  - 2533
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We study a dynamic general equilibrium model in which firms choose their investment level and capital structure, trading off the tax advantages of debt against the risk of costly default. Bankruptcy costs are endogenous, as bankrupt firms are forced to liquidate their assets, resulting in a fire sale if the market is illiquid. When the corporate income tax rate is positive, firms have a unique optimal capital structure. In equilibrium, firms default with positive probability and their assets are liquidated at fire-sale prices. The equilibrium features underinvestment and is constrained inefficient. In particular there is too little debt and default.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhv016
ER  - 



